LaPoynor ISD would like to welcome Kris Hutchins to our staff!!

My name is Kris Hutchins. I live in Poynor with my wife Amy and 3 kids Bailey 11th grade, Mary 8th grade and Gavin 6th grade! My wife and are both LaPoynor grads and bleed purple and white! I am also the Youth& Worship Pastor at FBC Poynor and have been a youth communicator for the last 10+ Years through several different formats and platforms. I am beyond excited and feel extremely blessed to come back home to LISD as the new Technology Director and PEIMS Coordinator. #FlyerPride

The Beginning of the 2020 School Year

LaPoynor ISD would like to welcome Ashley Faucett to our staff!!

My name is Ashley Faucett and I have been in education for 13 years. Before I came to LaPoynor, I was a first grade teacher for five years, an elementary counselor for two years, and a district counselor for five years. I have been married to Josh Faucett for 12 years and we have four precious children who will be joining the LaPoynor team! Ava will be in fourth grade, Brylie will be in Kinder, Hattie will be in PreK and Stolz will be in the daycare center. We are excited to start a new journey and can‚Äôt wait to see what this year will hold!

post_text:
Day 2
Secondary Parents and Students:

This is Crystal Woodard, Secondary Principal of LaPoynor ISD. Here it is, Day 2 of remote learning. As always, I pray for your family‚Äôs safety and good health and hope everyone is doing well. Let me begin by saying, Thank you for your patience and understanding as we work through the many facets of education for you or your child. We are working through the bumps and hope to maneuver to a comfortable ride very soon.

I hope things went a little smoother today in the process and the teachers were able to help assist your questions. If you are still having issues please feel free to contact one of us and we will do our best to correct the problem.

The practice of good hand washing and social distancing is working in ways we do not always see right away. Keep it going! We miss every one of our students and look forward to having our hallways full again, so keep your distance and wash your hands!

Due to the recent cancellation of the 2020 Henderson County Livestock Show scheduled to take place next week, the students of LaPoynor ISD have 68 market pigs on feed. As a chapter, we are working to help students recuperate at least some of the cost associated with their project. We are asking businesses or community members to consider purchasing one of these pigs for $300 each. If you choose to do so, you may take it home, have it processed (for an additional cost ‚Äì message us for details), or just make a donation that would be divided evenly among all LaPoynor FFA market exhibitors.
Please text Brad Rogers if you are interested or have further questions. 903-676-6458

A STOPPED SCHOOL BUS: WHAT DO I DO?

Texas State law requires that drivers stop when a school bus is operating a visual signal-either red flashing lights or extended stop arm (TRC 545.066). However, many Texas drivers are uncertain as to when they need to stop for a school bus.

Here are a few guidelines to reduce driver confusion, thus providing a safer environment for our children. #BackToSchoolSafety
Via Texas Department of Public Safety - Southeast Texas Region

shared_text:
Prayers For Emma
May 8, 2018 at 7:39 PM ¬∑

We are devastated and shaking as we write this, but trying to be strong for Emma.

She is bleeding in her stomach due to Graft Versus Host Disease (GVHD) of both her liver and stomach. Her blood counts continue to go down every 2 hours. This is very bad as they are already critically low. She is bleeding internally in her stomach. Tomorrow, they will sedate her do a colonoscopy and endoscopy to try to stop the bleeds. Even if its stopped, it won't cure anything. GVHD happens because Emma's body is rejecting her bone marrow transplant. This can be fatal.

We are at a complete loss right now. We are so heartbroken. We are in absolute fear. We need a miracle. We cannot loose her. Im so so sorry Emma. You deserve so much more.

Even if its stopped, it won't cure anything. GVHD happens because Emma's body is rejecting her bone marrow transplant. This can be fatal.

post_text: Elementary to Have Guest Speaker~Eddie Bowman, aka Chester Drawers - Author Eddie Bowman, a.k.a Chester Drawers will be coming to the LaPoynor on February 14th in the New Gym at 8:00 a.m. Students will have an opportunity to meet Eddie Bowman, Author, Entertainer, and Motivational Speaker from Southwest Missouri. Eddie uses interesting visual aids to inspire children to do their best while striving for worthwhile goals. He strongly believes that good values are essential for happiness and success. He will appear as "Chester Drawers" and will bring his guitar and sing songs, such as "Silly Dog", "Gravy on a Bucket Lid", and "Crazy Cat". Eddies' books will be on display, and he will autograph every book purchased. This is sure to be a great event for the kids to remember! http://edl.io/n817898

post_text: Driveway Work - Tomorrow, January 9th, the highway dept. will be attaching our driveways to the access road for the school. They will begin with the high school drive and move down from there. Once they finish one it will be open for vehicles. Please be patient during this process and watch carefully. http://edl.io/n804132
